Declare a constant for π and print it.

Show how to declare an immutable variable.

Reassign a mutable variable and display both values.

Demonstrate shadowing by reusing the same name for a new type.

Show shadowing in an inner scope that doesn’t affect the outer scope.

Contrast a constant with an immutable variable.

Explain why constants must have a type annotation.

Create a variable, shadow it as a different type, and print both.

Attempt to mutate an immutable variable and observe the compiler error.

Discuss when you would prefer a constant versus shadowing.
